Cloudy- e wind at 7 mph- 72 F
Cloudy- 80 F- northwest wind at 12 mph
Sunny- n wind at 5 mph- 74 F
Cloudy- 60 F- SW wind at 5 mph
Calm; it had rained on 5/18. 59 degrees air temp. Many fishermen; clear.
mostly cloudy; slight NW wind; few fishermen; cool the previous week with some rain; 74 degrees
sunny; slight chop; previous 3 days were very windy- rainy- cold
calm;light frost last night; sunny; surface water temp 73; air temp 71
overcast- calm- slight ripple.  Previous day very windy with white caps.  Air temp. 62.  Previous week air temp. in the low 60's
Calm- clear- sunny.  Last three days warm (75-85).  Some rain at night.  Present temp. 80
90 sunny lake stinks dead fish floating
Partly sunny. Last week temps mostly in the '50s- 10 to 15 degrees below normal. Today 10-15 MPH winds- temp. 74- first warm day
Sunny- 68 degrees. Cold weather last few days.  Highs in the 50s + 60s; 40s at night   Sunny; air temp 68; last few days 50's + 60's by day  and 40's at night
Sunny- 75 degrees no significent rain for 5 weeks  Temps. above average this week
Partly sunny; light wind- light chop; air temp. 76
mostly cloudy; light wind- slight chop; air temp 79
sunny; air temp. 82; light breeze; over 3" rain during week before testing
Choppy; rainy the last 3 days; cloudy
Overcast;rain last 2 days; 58 degrees; water temp at surface 66.3
Heavy rain last night; partly sunny today; in 90's for 2 days; temp now 79
Sunny; slight wind; rain yesterday + last night
Sunny; still; heavy rain previous week
Overcast; unseasonably warm; windy; slight chop; air temp 80
Sunny; calm; air temp 80; 10mph winds; light chop
Very windy; heavy chop; white caps; air temp 75; sunny
sunny rare white caps- breezy air temp 55 F ice off was April 10
sunny clear no wind - 7 mph small waves  52 F
clear- light wind- lots of rain lately - 5 inches in 10 days
bright. clear day  calm wind air temp 55 degrees   leaves in full color

8 inches of rain in the week before the readings.  Lots of algae along the shore and some small floating debris including a small island like piece of cattails and other vegetation  Lake is 6 inches higher than normal.

got 8 inches of rain last weekend.  Lake level very high 6-8 inches over normal  Some algae in water by docks.  Sunny with light north wind when we took measurements.  Four baby loons recently hatched from 2 nests out of 4.  Maybe one more pair on the way

clear air temp 65 degrees- cooler than normal for last week-  1 inch rain on July 20  4 loon chicks on lake.  No eagles born in nest on Frog Island this year again and no indication any eagles are claiming it for next year. So far no indication southern naiad mats and amount of southern naiad seems down quite a bit.  Rusty crayfish population in continuing decline. Lots of butterflies this year.  especially white admirals and fritillaries.
still- warm and humid.  air temp 82.7   rained 1/4 inch last night  lots of gulls and loons.  out of 4 pairs on lake 2 pair are raising 4 loon offspring.

temperature around 75 with light south wind 5 to 8 miles per hour.  some fair weather cumulus clouds.  Very little boat traffic.  birds migrating no rain for 7+ days  as usual Roger Larson recording data
air temp 65- partly cloudy- wind NW at 3 to 5 mph.   Trees starting to turn- yesterday and day before very windy.  2 days ago- 2.25 inches of rain.

Peak color on maples. Rained 1 inch day before and very windy for a few hours.  saw one loon-   fishing very slow  air temp 46 and wind 5 to 7 mph at time we took observations. Roger Larson first mate
Partly cloudy- air temp 70 degrees- wind 10+ mph- gusts to 20 mph-  some whithecaps
calm- air temp 85- clear with some high cirrus- limited rain in last 3 weeks and limited wind in last week- no waves today
cloudless- wind 5 to 9 mph 65 degrees- some rain in the last 3 days- 3+ inches in the last 2 weeks.
went out with Sandy Wickman doing multiple samples for quality testing- Cloudy- 63 degrees- no rain in the last week- winds 5 to 10- waves 6 inches

went out on sunny fairly calm day to try to get a better secchi  disk reading because the last one seemed low. top of lake temp had fallen to 64.8  new result showed turnover in progress since this reading even lower.
clear sky- 69 degrees- generally dry and warm in the last week.  wind 10 mph- choppy- few whitecaps.
Much rain and wind in the last week.  turn over on going.  Today partly cloudy- wind 10 + mph  air temp 54 degrees F

column1: Fall foliage just past peak by a day.  lake beautiful and empty.  Lots of turkey and deer around.

column2: mostly cloudy- air temp about 50  North wind 8-10 mph following 7 days of warm and sunny weather.  1.5 inches of rain 3 days ago
cloudy- some sun- rained .1 inch in thunderstorm yesterday-  weather unsettled- light wind from north 65 degree air temp.  ice off lake on April 29.  no chem testing in May due to corona virus

sunny and warm- air temp high 70s  calm to light breeze- no boat traffic-  adult loons only present  .25 inch of rain yesterday in tiny thunderstorms- in 80s for the past week-  fairly dry until last couple of days.
sunny to partly sunny-  rain 2-3 inches to days ago.  75 degrees- waves 6-12 inches- no whitecaps but wind 10 mph  level of lake up about 4 inches. lots of eagles saw 5 during this trip
sunny and windy- temps falling 60 to 65 degrees- 1.7 inches in last week rain.
52 degrees- partly cloudy- follows 3 day warm period- light north wind- 4 inches of rain in last 2 weeks.  oaks and poplars in full color- maples losing leaves-  2 loons on lake
